- Always include typing when writing python functions for both inputs and outputs
- Always use Optional[...] for arguments that can be None
- Use TypeVar for generic functions i.e `T = TypeVar('T')
- Use Callable for functions as arguments
- Use list[str] and similar instead of List[str] or Dict[str]
- Write python as if we are using 3.12+ python best practices